ChooseParameter.Other: polymer resin was deagassed under vacuum to remove bubbles
polymer material was spincoated onto the copper plate using a Specialty Coating Systems spin coater
breakdown testing at room temperature and at 200C was carried out in Dow Corning 561 silicone transformer fluid
breakdown testing at 300C was carried out in DuPont Krytox XHT-1000 PFPE (perfluoropolyether) oil held in a glass petri dish. For testing above room temperature
copper plates 0.8 – 1.0 mm thick were electropolished in a waterphosphoric acid solution to remove surface contamination and surface oxides while keeping the surface-scratch free
potential of 1.5 V was applied on the immersed copper plate for 5 min
copper plate removed from acid solution and immersed in distilled water and two separate beakers of ethanol
copper plates stored in dessicator prior to curing to minimize oxide formation
